        <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>cb</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The expiry callback function of type k_timer_expiry_t </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>pUser</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to the owner of the timer (normally this pointer of task) </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>duration</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para><ref refid="class_timer" kindref="compound">Timer</ref> duration in seconds </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>period</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para><ref refid="class_timer" kindref="compound">Timer</ref> period in seconds for cyclic timer, default is 0 (not a cyclic timer)</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
The constructor initializes a timer, prior to its first use by calling function k_timer_init provided by the operating system, which assign the expiry callback function and returns the timer administration structure timer_handle. It set the owner of the timer by calling function k_timer_user_data_set also provided by the operating system and initializes the protected varaibles duration and period. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
